iggest challenges is that not all biodegradable plastics are created equal, and some types of biodegradable plastics may not break down as quickly or completely as others. In addition, the composting of biodegradable plastics may require special facilities and conditions that are not widely available, making it difficult for some communities to properly manage biodegradable plastic waste.',
